  "texts": [
    "For a Gaussian Mixture Model (GMM) to indicate extreme values score in time series data number of components (n_components) is set to 3, allowing the model to capture both data distributions.",
    "Initialization is done using k-means (init_params) for better starting points.",
    "The maximum number of iterations (max_iter) is set between 100 and 1000 to ensure convergence, with a convergence threshold around 1e-3 to 1e-6 for precise fitting.",
    "Regularization of the covariance matrix (reg_covar) with values from 1e-6 to 1e-4 ensures numerical stability.",
    "Results and discussionThe predictive capacity and consistency of the proposed framework is assessed about state-of-the-art DNNs used for time series forecasting and are examined through three specific research questions outlined below:• Research Question 1: Does this strategy generalize to datasets of multiple domains?• Research Question 2: How effectively does our model adapt to and perform on previously unencountered data?• Research Question 3: How accurate are the predictions for extreme values?"
  ],
